      • fileMenuDialog

        public java.lang.String[] fileMenuDialog()
        Method allowing to display the file manager window. It displays the filename and content TextViews.
        Returns:
        an array of String where the first element ([0]) represents the filename as a String and the second element ([1]) represents the file's content (as a String too). If the user has clicked on "cancel", it returns "null".

      • addNodeToLastInsertedNode

        public void addNodeToLastInsertedNode(java.lang.Object newNodeObject,
                                      int level)
                               throws NoPreviousInsertedNodeException,
                                      LevelException
        Method allowing to insert a new element/node directly to a node that has just been inserted before.
        Parameters:
        newNodeObject - the new node object to add to the tree.
        level - the level of the new element/node to insert. The level must be always greater than zero. For example, level=1 if it is the child of the selected node, level=2 if it is the child of this last one, and so on).
        Throws:
        NoPreviousInsertedNodeException - throws a NoPreviousInsertedNodeException if no node has been inserted before.
        LevelException - throws a LevelException if the level is a negative value or zero.
